      "stimulus_html": "",
      "stem_html": "<p>Acid-catalyzed dehydration of 2,2-dimethylcyclohexanol yields a mixture of 1,2-dimethylcyclohexene and isopropylidenecyclopentane. Propose a mechanism to account for the formation of both products.</p>\n<img class=\"scaled-down\" src=\"https://exercises.openstax.org/rails/active_storage/blobs/proxy/eyJfcmFpbHMiOnsibWVzc2FnZSI6IkJBaHBBc01WIiwiZXhwIjpudWxsLCJwdXIiOiJibG9iX2lkIn19--cf0e7ca6144c7f10971de46f224a3ec852a04e92/OChem_17_EC_021.jpg\" alt=\"The structure of isopropylidenecyclopentane. It is an isocyclopentane with a double bond between C 1 of cyclopentane and C 2 of the propyl group.\">",
